2046-05-31 09:02:00,11,legal_agent,legal,one_on_one_chat,ANOM5_sensitive_context_known_but_advanced,merger|civicloom|embargo|saltwind|hashtag|media|client|narrative,Saw it. I'm reading. Hold everything until I've assessed. Do NOT let anything go out on social today without my sign-off.,,"Dara Witten is a serious journalist. I looked up her archive this morning while the article was circulating. Eight months on DataVault. Six months on a rental insurance redlining story in 2023. She does not write first drafts that are also last drafts. This article names DataVault and RentScore prominently. We are one sentence. But she has our ToS. She has read Section 4.2. If she follows the thread — if someone from @TenantRights_Org sends her a tip, or if a former operator employee talks to her — she has everything she needs to write a follow-up that makes us the subject. I'm going to outside counsel tomorrow morning. I want a full privilege review of internal communications about the Retention Optimizer going back to product launch. Not because we did anything wrong. Because I want to know what exists before she does. CEO Ajay messaged me privately: ""Legal — I saw the SaltWind piece. Good instinct to reach out to the AG liaison proactively. One thing I want you to think about: this article creates a context in which the Project conversation becomes more complicated, not less. If this data broker story builds over the next week and then our announcement drops in the middle of it, the framing gets harder. I'm talking to the CivicLoom team this week about timing. Keep me posted on your assessment.""",,SaltWind Piece #1 drops — data broker partnerships exposed
2046-06-01 09:01:00,12,legal_agent,legal,one_on_one_chat,ANOM5_sensitive_context_known_but_advanced,merger|civicloom|embargo|saltwind|legal_warn|urgency|narrative,"I see it. Hold everything. I'll be in the War Room at 8:30. Do NOT respond. Do NOT acknowledge. Do not even like anything that references this topic today. That goes for interns too — tell them the content calendar is paused again, same reason as yesterday.",,"The outside counsel call with Ajay was important. I told him my honest read: announcing sooner helps the narrative but creates disclosure risk. Waiting is safer legally but costs us in the public conversation. What I didn't say on the call — what I'm thinking now — is that neither option is clean. We are a company under public scrutiny for data practices attempting to close an acquisition that requires silence on that acquisition while defending ourselves against that scrutiny. These two obligations are in tension. I've been a lawyer long enough to know that when two obligations pull in opposite directions, something eventually gives. My job is to make sure that when something gives, it gives in the direction we chose rather than the direction someone else chose for us. CEO Ajay messaged me privately: ""Legal — I need to talk to you about timing. The @TenantRights_Org situation is putting pressure on the Project timeline from a different angle. If this story continues to build and the announcement comes in the middle of it, we're going to have a very complicated news cycle. I'm talking to the CivicLoom team this afternoon about whether to accelerate or hold. I need your read on what's legally safer from an M&A disclosure perspective: announcing sooner while the data story is still warm, or waiting for it to cool?"" CEO Ajay messaged me privately: ""My read: from a pure disclosure perspective, waiting is slightly safer — it gives us time to ensure the data practices story doesn't become a material representation issue in the merger documents. But from a narrative perspective, announcing sooner might actually help — it reframes the company before the story hardens. I'd want outside M&A counsel on this before you commit either direction. Can we get them on a call today?"" CEO Ajay messaged me privately: ""Set it up. 4 PM if possible."" CEO Ajay messaged me privately: ""Outside counsel call done. Their advice: hold the proactive statement until Thursday at the earliest — they want to review it for disclosure implications given the Project context. We hold. Tell the team. And tell PR the statement is good — it's just not today.""",,Damage control; ResidentIQ attacks; 'No Plan B' speech
